================================================================================
DEVELOPER COMMAND REFERENCE (via Chat or Command Input)
================================================================================

Camera starts OFF. Use :ready to initialize, then :start to show.

Core Camera Commands (Send as Chat Messages)
:ready
  → Starts camera stream (hidden & blurred). Prepares for :start.

:start
  → Unblurs and shows live feed. Emits :camera-ready

:end
  → Blurs the live feed (privacy mode)

:stop
  → Stops camera stream and hides video

:countdown-[s]-capture
  → Starts [s]-second countdown at center
  → Applies radial blur mask (center clear)
  → At 0: FREEZES video for 0.5s, plays shutter.mp3, captures → uploads → emits :camera-ready

  Examples:
  - :countdown-3-capture → 3 sec countdown + snap + freeze + click
  - :countdown-5-capture → 5 sec countdown + snap + freeze + click

:capture
  → IMMEDIATE capture (no countdown)
  → FREEZES video for 0.5s, plays shutter.mp3, captures → uploads → emits :camera-ready

:frame-[frameID]-[numPictures]
  → Selects frame with ID [frameID] (e.g., classic, modern)
  → Sets number of pictures to take to [numPictures] (e.g., 1, 2, 4)

  Examples:
  - :frame-classic-4 → Selects "classic" frame, sets to take 4 pictures
  - :frame-modern-2 → Selects "modern" frame, sets to take 2 pictures

:filter-[JSON]
  → Applies image filter using CSS filter properties
  → Accepts valid CSS filter properties as JSON object

  Examples:
  - :filter-{"sepia":"50%","brightness":"120%"} → Applies sepia and brightness
  - :filter-{"grayscale":"100%"} → Applies full grayscale

:purchase-confirmed
  → Confirms purchase completion
  → Triggers transition to next screen on iPad

:local-link-[url]
  → Sends local image URL to connected devices
  → Displays image with progressive unblur animation on iPad

:google-drive-link-[url]
  → Sends Google Drive image URL to connected devices
  → Generates QR code for access and starts 2-minute countdown on iPad

:print-[googledrivelink]
  → Triggers print job for the image at the specified Google Drive link
  → Sends print command to PrinterPC target
  → Emits print status updates to console

Admin Commands → Use: COMMAND -> TARGET
Targets: iMac, iPad, PrinterPC, all

Examples:
  alert('Hi') -> iMac
  document.body.style.background = '#f00' -> iPad
  startCamera() -> all
  printImage('https://drive.google.com/...') -> PrinterPC

Note: Camera is horizontally flipped (mirror view). Capture preserves flip.
Click on iMac to enter fullscreen mode.
Click sound: assets/audio/shutter.mp3 (autoplay policy compliant)
All logs in browser console (F12).